thanks for the debug output. as we can see there, gcc_init and all the other init code is called twice (even with same PID!). this shouldn't happen, and might be the cause of the crash.
it looks to me as if Mac OS X' implementation of pthread_once() is buggy.

here is a simplified test case
```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <pthread.h>

pthread_once_t init_once = PTHREAD_ONCE_INIT;

static void do_init(void) {
	dprintf(2, "this message should be printed only once\n");
}

__attribute__((constructor))
static void gcc_init(void) {
        pthread_once(&init_once, do_init);
}
```
